<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19104] Standardize tablestats formatting and data units</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19104</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tablestats reports output in plaintext, JSON or YAML. The human readable output currently has a mix of KiB, bytes with inconsistent spacing&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simplify and default output to &apos;human readable&apos;. Machine readable output is available as an option and the current mixed output formatting is neither friendly for human or machine reading and can be replaced.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/attach/noimage.png&quot; imagetext=&quot;image-2023-11-27-13-49-14-247.png&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Not a goal now (consider a follow up Jira):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix inconsistencies with KiB/MiB/GiB and KB/MB/GB formatting:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;gcstats - uses MB&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getcompactionthroughput - uses MB/s&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getstreamthroughput - uses MB/s&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;info - uses MiB/GiB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
