                            <comment id="17791743" author="bschoeni" created="Thu, 30 Nov 2023 19:02:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zaaath&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zaaath&quot;&gt;zaaath&lt;/a&gt; great, we should email the mailing list to confirm agreement on this format change.&#160; But it seems obviously a good idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17792140" author="JIRAUSER303078" created="Fri, 1 Dec 2023 17:17:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt; Got it, I&apos;ll do it once I figure out how it&apos;s done.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the current goal of refactoring the human-readable output, could you confirm that this is your expectation. If it&apos;s not, feel free to comment here or directly in the spreadsheet: &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1tbsldoGWduKpAxxX7Jsv5jCcLw3FsFA8lTHB_Coli1E/edit&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1tbsldoGWduKpAxxX7Jsv5jCcLw3FsFA8lTHB_Coli1E/edit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The spreadsheet contains the current nodetool output and the next iteration side-by-side, differences are highlighted using conditional formatting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793032" author="bschoeni" created="Mon, 4 Dec 2023 21:03:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zaaath&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zaaath&quot;&gt;zaaath&lt;/a&gt; Jacek Lewandowski suggests &quot;limiting the number of significant digits to 3 in the human readable format.&quot; In the above example it would translate to:&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Space used (live): 1.46 TiB&lt;br/&gt;
Space used (total): 1.46 TiB&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Bytes repaired: 0.00 KiB&lt;br/&gt;
Bytes unrepaired: 4.31 TiB&lt;br/&gt;
