&lt;p&gt;I think that makes sense for units with order of magnitude.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793079" author="JIRAUSER303078" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2023 01:56:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for mentioning Jacek&#8217;s preferences here. I updated the spreadsheet, but ran into some ambiguities applying the Jacek&apos;s rule.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt; How should the following cases be handled to satisfy the req:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;579.280 MiB (the current &#8220;human-readable&#8221; output: 607419608 bytes)&lt;br/&gt;
Options: 579 MiB, 579.28 MiB, or 0.57 GiB?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;32.034 MiB (the current &#8220;human-readable&#8221; output: 33590024 bytes)&lt;br/&gt;
Options: 32.0 MiB, 32.03 MiB, or 0.03 GiB?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Also, is it possible for me to see the full discussion with Jacek? Is it in a mail list or Slack?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stefan.miklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stefan.miklosovic&quot;&gt;stefan.miklosovic&lt;/a&gt; How does this Nodetool output formatting look to you? Feel free to comment here or directly in the spreadsheet &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1tbsldoGWduKpAxxX7Jsv5jCcLw3FsFA8lTHB_Coli1E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1tbsldoGWduKpAxxX7Jsv5jCcLw3FsFA8lTHB_Coli1E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793296" author="bschoeni" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2023 14:09:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jacek&apos;s comments are on the mailing list [dev@cassandra.apache.org|&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/list.html?dev@cassandra.apache.org&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/list.html?dev@cassandra.apache.org&lt;/a&gt;.]&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The units TB, KB, MB, GB are based on the thousands separator (i.e, when you have more than three digits), so&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) 579 MiB&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) 32.0 MiB&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) 3.79 MiB&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You would never use 0.57 GiB as that would be the wrong units, it should be in MiB.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793425" author="JIRAUSER303078" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2023 20:37:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That makes sense, I&apos;ve updated the spreadsheet. And thank you for starting the conversation in the mailing list.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt; I think the following fields are missing byte quantifiers:&lt;/p&gt;

